What you need:
* Raspberry Pi 4
    * https://geni.us/BmCeEgp (kit with everything you need) 
* External Hard Drive
    * https://geni.us/zAMSS (Samsung SSD) 
* (optional) Geekworm Kit
    * Case: https://geni.us/YfACT1
    * Cooling Expansion Board: https://geni.us/sqU6EW
    * SATA expansion board: https://geni.us/9RQAaM
    * Power Adapter: https://geni.us/LTLOHJ
    * Internal SSD: https://geni.us/Gdahek9

STEP 1 - Bake your Pi
Raspberry Pi Imager: https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/
1. Update your Pisudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade

STEP 2 - Install OpenMediaVault
1. Run this command:
wget -O - https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenMediaVault-Plugin-Developers/installScript/master/install | sudo bash

INSTALL PLEX MEDIA SERVER
1. Install the https-transport packagesudo apt-get install apt-transport-https
2. Add the Plex repositoriescurl https://downloads.plex.tv/plex-keys/PlexSign.key | sudo apt-key add -
3. 
4. echo deb https://downloads.plex.tv/repo/deb public main | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/plexmediaserver.list
5. 
6. sudo apt-get update
7. Install Plexsudo apt install plexmediaserver
